          content_en: 'Of the six main hormones we covered in the first lesson, one plays an especially crucial role in the modern world: **dopamine**. People who think dopamine is "the happiness hormone" are wrong. It isn\'t. It\'s the hormone of **expected reward**. And this detail changes everything — because it explains why modern technology has such a strong influence on our motivation and behavior.\n\nWhen you take a bite of chocolate, dopamine levels rise a bit. But surprisingly, the biggest dopamine release happens at the moment you know about the chocolate and are about to reach for it. Dopamine doesn\'t respond to pleasure itself — it responds to the expectation of pleasure. That\'s why "traveling" is often more fun than "being there," and why online shopping feels like a reward even when the package then sits in your closet for a week.',
